<br />

<br />
Well I have no official word on the status/classification of each item yet but if we were to look at the frequency of firepet use, We rarely use the fire pet on raids as its root and debuff spells cause havoc. 
<br />

<br />
We rarely use the fire pet solo cause the darn thing is always picking the worst friggen times to rebuff itself and if you have to quick cast it to your aid, it just sits there and buffs itself while laughing at you getting pounded by a bunch of mobs.   
<br />

<br />
No to mention that the thing still runs out of mana too fast. About the only good thing is that the nukes hit pretty hard and we can use it to really piss off the wizzys with an ice comet show (although the last time I used it the darn thing would cast ice comet for anything) 
<br />

<br />
Put it in the same catageory as bristlebanes bundle as its just for show most of the time. (not all but most)
<br />

<br />
Would I be correct to represent that 99% of us don't use it in 99% of the encounters we face? 
<br />

<br />
I'd say that if SoE looks at the 1% as a reason to say it's working as intended, I'll just give them a free ride in my car to the local sanitarium.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.cox.net/dtresendes/danisig.png" border="0" />
