			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My one concern in seeing all the correspondence on the official boards, as well as here on the Mage's Tower, is the dilution of opinions.
<br />

<br />
I really got concerned when I saw pet healing abilities ranked higher than pet DPS (this was later changed, it seems).
<br />

<br />
And I really scratched my head over the requests for CoH changes.  Believe me, I agree 100%.  But, if I have 1 minute of a dev's day (which I honestly think, as many people and class representatives and so forth post), the one point I want to drive home is: 
<br />

<br />
Mages are a DPS class by design (either sourced from the EQ Live site, or by examining our abilities and those we lack).  We have far too little as for defense or for non-bot (summoning pet gear could be done with some intelligent macros, for example) utility, and this must either change into a blending of class lines (root, snare, charm, or any of the myriad requests), or a solidification of the view that in return for our sacrifices, we have superiour sustained DPS and arguably impressive burst DPS.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I am against any class line blurring, and would like to see us truly as respected damage dealers, something that might not out nuke a wizard on a single nuke basis, or out damage a rogue on a 2 hour parse, but give both a run for the money (which would put us into a "hybrid DPS" role, where we have both burst and long term DPS use).  I am against "priest nuke encroachment" just as I am against "hybrid pet encroachment" (any other class with a pet).
<br />

<br />
After that, fixing CoH, zoning pets, healing ratios, even AAXP are just cherries on top.
<br />

<br />
Dyrauelene</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
