			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think that a mana constrained high dps nuking fire pet would be an excellent idea.
<br />

<br />
It should be perma-rooted (movable by summon companion), and should have the spell line-up changed so that it no longer roots, dispells or does AE damage. Instead, it would be nice to see it do a selection of nukes or dots (not just fire based) for a relatively high DPS (say 140 unfocused).
<br />

<br />
Such a pet would need a reasonable sized mana pool (say 2.5/3k mana), which should be scalable based on the focus used to summon it (say an extra 300 per increase in lvl, and increased mana regen).  A focused pet should also get access to higher level nukes increasing its DPS.
<br />

<br />
Then, the pet would act as a high DPS dot spell that does not aggro the casting mage. Since the pet would not require buffs or equipment to do maximum damage, it would be a prime candidate for reclaiming/chaining, once out of mana to achieve more sustainable DPS.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
