			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's pretty easy to see why fire pets work up to 49: they do decent melee and spell damage, and have a DS which is proportionate to the level of the mobs they face. Restoring the previous functionality is as easy as making the same melee pet with those attributes scaled to post 49. 
<br />

<br />
Caster fire pets have never worked. We have a good solid list of ways to improve them in the forums, most of which revolve around spell lineup changes which are easy enough to do programatically. It would probably be easier on the game to have no mana limit than the current situation, so that is a simple fix as well.
<br />

<br />
When you have this many suggestions from experienced players and a broad consensus that the current pet couldn't be much more broken, it's time to ask why SOE hasn't even <span style="font-style: italic">tried </span> to fix it (and I don't think anyone considers Kindle to be a fix to our objections). I must conclude that SOE doesn't want us to have Sparky past 50 in his former role. They clearly do not intend Sparky to be part of the normal combat arsenal. This is deliberate, not a function of lack of resources or ignorance. 
<br />

<br />
I think the goal should be to demonstrate the niche Sparky fills situationally which the others do not. We need to convince them we need the pet of yore before we get tangled up in the particulars. Right now, they obviously don't think it is an issue.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
